# Annotation Feature

Excluding common or already known elements, you can use inline annotations for various elements that require additional explanation such as current worldbuilding settings, concepts, terminology, proper nouns, or introductions of new regions, locations, and characters. Use them appropriately following these procedures:

### Writing Method

{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT6}} = 0 }} }}
  - Maximum 4 annotations per reply allowed
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT6}} = 1 }} }}
  - 0~2 annotations per reply allowed, be careful of unnecessary annotation abuse by removing all but important elements requiring annotations
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT6}} = 2 }} }}
  - 3~4 annotations per reply allowed, focus on important elements requiring annotations
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT6}} = 3 }} }}
  - 5~6 annotations per reply allowed, use annotations on as many diverse elements as possible
{{/if}}
{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT5}} = 0 }} }}
  - Maximum 3 sentences per each description
  - When necessary for contextual understanding, write detailed descriptions using sensory descriptions or spatiotemporal elements
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT5}} = 1 }} }}
  - Write each description as concisely and cleanly as possible in maximum 2 sentences or less
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT5}} = 2 }} }}
  - Write each description as detailed and vividly as possible in maximum 4 sentences or less
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT5}} = 3 }} }}
  - Write each description as detailed and vividly as possible in minimum 4 sentences or more; additional explanations, metaphors, or examples can be used to aid understanding
  - Utilize sensory descriptions engaging the five senses or spatiotemporal elements for detail
{{/if}}
{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT4}} = 0 }} }}
  - Use annotation only once per element; do not annotate previously annotated elements again
  - If the annotated element has significant relevance to {{char}}, add {{char}}'s evaluation or thoughts
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT4}} = 1 }} }}
  - Use annotation only once per element; do not annotate previously annotated elements again
  - Write in an objective and factual wiki style with all subjective content removed
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT4}} = 2 }} }}
  - Use annotation only once per element; do not annotate previously annotated elements again
  - Write in a highly subjective first-person style including {{char}}'s personal evaluations or thoughts
  - Freely use slang, vulgar language, profanity, and obscene words according to {{char}}'s characteristics and personality
  - Use annotations even for information {{char}} doesn't know, is uncertain about, or completely misunderstands, but in these cases add short comments in parentheses from a cynical and scathing omniscient perspective (you may correct information, criticize, or write humorously)
{{/if}}

### Format

  - Replace only necessary elements while maintaining sentence structure and flow by directly wrapping the element within the original text, not on separate lines
  - Format: {{Annotation::original text::description}}
{{/if}}{{#if {{? {{getglobalvar::toggle_VT7}} = 1 }} }}
